sub_title: Text Editor, Writer, Translator and Instructor at Effective English
summary:
Teacher, trainer, writer, translator, editor, husband, father.  

Degrees:
—California at San Diego (Professional Copy Editing)
—Notre Dame (BA, Literature, International Studies)
—Tulane (MA, Latin American Studies, Humanities)

Clients:
—public and private sector
—finance, oil and gas 
—NGOs (Public Health)
—scholars (Humanities, social sciences, 'hard' sciences)
—business website development
—hifi audio

Recent projects:
—workshop leader for non-native English-language writers at various universities in Europe, Latin America and Southeast Asia
—various award applications
—several anthologies and single- and dual-author books ranging from business best practices to Roman archeology (and everything in between)
—hifi audio text revision
